
msgid "JSON encode escape forward slash"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"For some reason, in the upstream ``lua_cjson``, the '/' sign is escaped. But"
" according to the ``rfc4627`` standard, it is unnecessary and questionably "
"compatible with other implementations."
msgstr ""

msgid "Old and new behavior"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"By toggling the ``json_escape_forward_slash`` compat option, you can chose "
"either the json encoder escapes the '/' sign or it does not:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"tarantool> require('compat').json_escape_forward_slash = 'old'\n"
"---\n"
"...\n"
"\n"
"tarantool> require('json').encode('foo/bar')\n"
"---\n"
"- '\"foo\\/bar\"'\n"
"...\n"
"\n"
"tarantool> require('compat').json_escape_forward_slash = 'new'\n"
"---\n"
"...\n"
"\n"
"tarantool> require('json').encode('foo/bar')\n"
"---\n"
"- '\"foo/bar\"'\n"
"..."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The option affects both the global serializer instance and serializers "
"created with ``json.new()``. It also affects the way log messages are "
"encoded when written to the log in the json format (the "
"``box.cfg.log_format`` option is set to 'json')."
msgstr ""

msgid "Known compatibility issues"
msgstr ""

msgid "At this point, no incompatible modules are known."
msgstr ""

